parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The T21 emissions recall repair has caused a range of problems, including battery drain, loss of power, surging, and black smoke from the exhaust, which can lead to vehicle breakdowns, accidents, and financial losses.
symptoms: The backlight of the instrument panel remains illuminated after the vehicle is turned off
the battery dies overnight
the vehicle has no power
the vehicle surges
black smoke comes out of the exhaust
the EGR valve makes a buzzing noise when the car is off
and the auxiliary fan turns on but the vehicle won't start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to remain on even when the ignition key is turned off, leading to battery drain and potentially causing other electrical systems to malfunction.

potential malfunction of other electrical systems.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head lamp sensor can cause limited illumination when driving at night, increasing the risk of accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the resonator can cause a loss of power, potentially affecting vehicle performance and safety.

resonator failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tire valve stem can lead to tire pressure loss, which can cause tire failure, accidents, and injuries. The manufacturer's refusal to honor the recall can exacerbate the issue, leaving consumers at risk.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries. The failure to replace the tire can lead to further damage and increase the risk of an accident.
